option.name: Reportable Breach
option.help-text: A Reportable Breach is an error resulting in significant detriment or real risk of harm, wither due to the volume of data or its sensitivity and which the Director of Resources and Information Governance Lead decides in light of legal advice and in accordance with ICO Guidance should be reported to the ICO within 72 hours by the Data Protection Officer OR An incident that has been reported to the ICO by the complainant.

option.name: Major Breach
option.help-text: A security incident involving releasing RESTRICTED information outside the organisation. This is Personal and Special Category data or over 1,000 pieces of Personal Data.

option.name: Minor Breach
option.help-text: An incident involving PROTECTED information. This is Personal Information which includes sensitive information which is not released externally.
